history.content:
Hey guys I'm a junior transfer starting from this Fall and I just took 61A and 70 over the summer.

Right after the summer ended, I got to know about the necessity to prep coding interview on this upcoming Fall for an internship next Summer.

I have taken 2 semester of C++ before transferring(upto DSA) at a community college, and I will be taking 61B this fall.

Regarding to my current situation, I have two questions.

1. Do kind of coding interview problems vary depending on the company/position I am applying to?

    For an instance, would problems differ from Google and Nuro when I apply to same position such as SWE intern?

    Or would problem differ from Google's MLE intern and SWE intern?

2. As I have only a limited time, what would be the best way to optimize my time to prep for the September - October interview?

    What other ways exist besides working on Leetcode? My interest is in Autunomous vehicles.

Thank you so much for reading. If any of my questions are vauge, please let me know!
history.subject: Have limited time to prepare for coding interview
